-- Emera Sees Total C$6.2 Billion Investment in Newfoundland Power Project
-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 2010-11-18T13:19:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-18/emera-sees-total-c-6-2-billion-investment-in-newfoundland-power-project.html
 Emera Inc. said C$6.2 billion will
be invested “by all parties” in a project where Nalcor Energy
will will build generating facilities at Muskrat  Falls.  Emera and Nalcor will jointly develop transmission in
Newfoundland and Labrador to “enable the movement of Lower
Churchill energy” through a joint venture that is 71 percent
owned by Nalcor and 29 percent by  Emera which will establish a
new, regulated transmission utility in  Newfoundland and
Labrador.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  